<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice Premier Ends Visit to Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier Jiang Chunyun
left here for home today, winding up a four-day official visit to
Algeria.
</P>
<P>
Algerian President Liamine Zeroual met with Jiang this morning,
who was accompanied by several members of his delegation.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, both sides expressed satisfaction with the
good bilateral ties and their desire to further enhance
cooperation, particularly in economic and commercial fields.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also expressed their readiness for a better
coordination of their stances on international and regional issues.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation, led by Jiang, arrived here Saturday on
the final leg of an African tour, which had taken it to Mauritius,
Madagascar and Uganda.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Algerian Prime Minister Ahmed Ouyahia held talks
with Jiang on bilateral ties and international issues.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Jiang said that the Chinese government and
people attached great importance to developing friendly ties with
Algeria, and regarded highly the positive role played by Algeria
in international and regional arenas.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian Prime Minister praised the brilliant results
secured by China in enhancing its national economy, pointing out
that Algeria considers China a model of success in maintaining
political stability while achieving economic development.
</P>
<P>
Ouyahia affirmed that Algeria attaches great importance to
developing its economic cooperation with China, especially in the
field of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
During Jiang's visit, Algeria and China signed two agreements,
one on periodic political consultation and the other on economic
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and his accompanying delegation arrived in Algiers
Saturday afternoon for a four-day official visit at the invitation
of the Algerian government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
