<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Non-Government Science and Technological Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey by the China
Non-Governmental Science and Technology Entrepreneurs Association
shows that the number of non-government science and technology
enterprises has grown a great deal in the past several years.
</P>
<P>
This type of enterprises now number more than 90,000, and have
some two million employees, with technical personnel accounting
for 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, the annual income of this sector has
currently exceeded 300 billion yuan (about 37 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Non-government science and technology enterprises appeared
after the country adopted reform and opening-up policies in the
late 1970s. By now, many of them, such as the famous
Beida-Founders group company, have grown very competitive in the
international market.
</P>
<P>
The China Non-Governmental Science and Technology Entrepreneurs
Association was established in April of 1987, and held its 10th
anniversary celebration in Beijing today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
