<HEADLINE> China Announces List of Key Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- China's State Planning Commission
(SPC) today named 129 projects as "key national construction
projects" and announced policies that will ensure their smooth
operation.
</P>
<P>
The majority involve basic industries designated by the state
and include coal, railways, transport, aviation, iron and steel,
oil, electricity, water conservation, chemicals, petrochemicals,
construction materials, and automobiles.
</P>
<P>
Among them are four coal mine development projects in Shanxi
Province, a fertilizer plant in Nanjing, a cement factory in
Tianjin, 35 power generating projects, and 15 railway construction
projects.
</P>
<P>
SPC says that ministries, local governments, and financial
institutions need to concentrate their support, especially
financial, on these projects, and has asked all departments
concerned to restrict the approval of new projects that may divert
limited resources away from the key projects.
</P>
<P>
It also urged everyone involved to tackle problems like land,
equipment, water, and electricity for the key projects, on time.
</P>
<P>
Inappropriate fees on key projects should be strictly halted,
according to a directive issued by SPC today, and developers can
legally refuse to pay any arbitrary fees and fares, according to
the directive.
</P>
<P>
Builders are urged to keep costs down while ensuring quality of
work in the projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
