<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 14 Killed, 39 Injured in S.Africa's Minibus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen minibus taxi
occupants, including 12 foreigners, were killed and 39 people
injured when the taxi collided with a bus and lorry near
Komatipoort today in Mpumalanga Province.
</P>
<P>
According to the police, 13 died at the scene and the 14th in
hospital.
</P>
<P>
Among the victims, 10 were Mozambicans, two South Africans and
the remaining two were believed to be foreign nationals. All were
men.
</P>
<P>
The minibus collided with the lorry which was crossing the
Komatipoort-Mananga border post road and 20 kilometres away from
Komatipoort, said Mpumalanga police spokesman Captain Benjamin
Bhembe.
</P>
<P>
The minibus then span back down the road, where it was hit by
an oncoming bus, apparently resulting in most of the fatalities
and injuries.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen of the 25 people on board the minibus taxi were
killed instantly and the rest were seriously injured, while of
the 50 people aboard the bus, 27 were seriously injured,
including the driver, who was in a critical condition.
</P>
<P>
Four occupants in the lorry were unscathed.
</P>
<P>
Further details of those killed and injured were not available.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
