<HEADLINE> China's Top Paper Producer Listed on Shenzhen Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The Jilin Paper Co. Ltd, China's
top paper producer, today had 60 million A shares listed on the
Shenzhen Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The stocks were issued at a per share price of 6.45 yuan in
late March, and raised 376 million in capital.
</P>
<P>
Funds generated by the sale will be used to develop special
types of high-quality paper, which is imported at present,
according to a company official.
</P>
<P>
Jilin Paper has an annual production capacity of 200,000 tons,
and its profits increased 14 percent last year to almost 100
million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
