<DOCNO> XIE19970409.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hun Sen Starts Visit of Laos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Lao official news agency, KPL, said Hun Sen and his
16-member delegation were greeted by Lao Prime Minister Khamtay
Siphandone, Vice Prime Minister Boung Nang Vorachit and other
members of the Lao Government and the National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Hun Sen is scheduled to hold talks with Lao
Prime Minister Khamtay Siphandone on bilateral cooperation, as
well as regional and international issues.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen will also meet Lao President of State Nouhak
Phoumsavan, and President of the National Assembly Saman Vinhaket.
</P>
<P>
The two sides are expected to sign three memoranda of
understanding on mine clearance in the border areas, cross-border
telecommunications and transportation, and Lao's Loumg Prabang and
Cambodia's Siem Reap becoming sister cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
