<HEADLINE> Prominent Chinese Businessman Dies During French Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The China Great Wall Industry
Corporation (CGWC) and the French National Space Research Center
(FNSRC) today jointly issued a statement about the death of Zhang
Tong, CGWC's president, during a visit to France's Guyana Space
Center.
</P>
<P>
According to the release, Zhang led a delegation to France on
March 8 at the invitation of the FNSRC to promote cooperation and
exchange between the two countries in space technology.
</P>
<P>
The FNSRC arranged a visit for Zhang and his delegation to the
Guyana Space Center on March 15, and visited the Salut Islands on
March 18, where he died in an accident.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the China National Aero-Industry
Corporation, CGWC, China's embassy in France, and Zhang's family
members and relatives visited the site of the accident, talked
with eye-witnesses, and read official documents provided by the
French side. The two sides reached an agreement on the cause of
Zhang's death.
</P>
<P>
According to the release, Zhang was accompanied by GSC
personnel. At Le Goff gulf, where he had stopped for a rest, he
was suddenly washed into the sea by a wave and drowned, after
rescue attempts failed.
</P>
<P>
Zhang's body was carried by Air France to Paris from Cayenne on
March 24.
</P>
<P>
According to the news release, the two sides have agreed that
Zhang's death was the result of an accident.
</P>
<P>
His hosts, the FNSRC, expressed deep sorrow and regret for the
unfortunate event and extended their condolences to Zhang's family
and relatives and to CGWC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
