<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sets Up Reserve System for Land Purchases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 8 (Xinhua) -- China's largest commercial center
is establishing a reserve system for land purchases that will try
to both standardize and invigorate real estate assets of
state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The system includes establishing a land development center
which is responsible for purchasing, replacing, and developing
idle land owned by bankrupt enterprises to support the
reorganization and reform of state-owned enterprises through the
market.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Land Development Center, the first of its kind in
China, has a loan of one billion yuan from the Shanghai Branch of
the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China, which will be used
for light industry, textiles, electronics, and the reorganization
of assets.
</P>
<P>
According to a local source, the Shanghai Land Development
Center will handle land and assets of over 100 enterprises that
have gone bankrupt in the past two years and oversee purchase,
replacement, transfer, and development of the land in relation to
readjustment of the industrial structure and the city's overall
development needs. 
</P>
