<HEADLINE> Zairean Warring Factions Agree Necessities to End </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Representatives from the
Zairean government and reble forces agreed today that an end to
hostilities in their country was necessary to bring about a
political solution to the ongoing civil war.
</P>
<P>
In a joint statement in Pretoria, the administrative capital
of South Africa, they said there was a need for fundamental and
democratic change in Zaire.
</P>
<P>
Peace talks between representatives of the Zairean government
and rebels led by Laurent-Desire Kabila in Pretoria have entered
the fourth day.
</P>
<P>
South African Deputy President Thabo Mbeki, who had played a
prominent role as peace broker, told reporters today that the
Zairean negotiators had had useful discussions on the timing and
modalities of ending hostilities.
</P>
<P>
"A process of consultation has already started with their
principles on this matter," South African Press Association
quoted Mbeki as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, Mbeki did not provide any details about the Zairean
peace talks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
