<HEADLINE> Islamic Jihad Vows to Carry on Suicide Attacks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The fundamentalist organization,
Islamic Jihad, declared today that it will continue to deal with
the "Jewish enemy" with what it called the weapon of martyrdom,
according to a report of JMCC, a Palestinian press service based
in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The threat of suicide attack was contained in a statement
distributed in the Palestinian territories by the armed wing of
Islamic Jihad.
</P>
<P>
"When the criminal (Binyamin) Netanyahu knows that nobody can
stop his settlements in any spot of what he calls the Land of
Israel," the statement said, "he should know together with the
(Palestinian) Autonomy Authority, our people, our nation and the
entire world that no one can stop or ban us from hitting any
Zionist target whatever it is in any spot of our occupied land."
</P>
<P>
The organization criticized the Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) for what it called collaboration with Israel to crack down
Jihad activities, saying that some 300 of Jihad members in Gaza
had recently been arrested and brutally tortured in prisons.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the Islamic Jihad demands that the PNA
stop jailing its members.
</P>
<P>
Under heavy pressure from Israel and the U.S., the PNA has
carried out a massive campaign to crack down the fundamentalist
groups, especially Islamic Jihad, in the wake of the recent
suicide bombing attacks in Tel Aviv and the Gaza Strip. 
</P>
</TEXT>
