<HEADLINE> Hydrogen Tank Explosion Kills 1, Injuries 30 in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 8 (Xinhua) -- A hydrogen tank at a vegetable oil
plant exploded, killing one man and injuring 30 in Babol, 150
kilometers northeast of Tehran, an informed source said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The source said that the massive explosion rocked the
northern city and its sound was heard in the port city of
Babolsar Monday.
</P>
<P>
The explosion of hydrogen tank in Shokoufeh Azadi vegetable
oil plant located at Serah-e Babolsar, Babol, resulted in damages
worth thousands of dollars, and the blast turned the factory into
a pile of rubble.
</P>
<P>
The force of the blast was so great that the building adjacent
to the factory were razed to ground and the window panes of
other homes in the vicinity were shattered.
</P>
<P>
Seyyed Taqi Mousavi, 34, was killed in the explosion. However,
no details are available on the condition of the injured. The
cause of the blast has yet to be ascertained by fire experts.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, there is no official media report about the
incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
