<HEADLINE> Perot Denied TV Time for Campaign Reform Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Ross Perot, two-time
presidential candidate, was turned down by the three major
television networks when he tried to purchase 30 minutes in prime
time to discuss campaign finance, Perot's political organization
said.
</P>
<P>
Perot offered to pay the full market price to air the program,
but ABC, CBS and NBC rejected the offer, Russel Verney, the Reform
Party national chairman, said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the program would have discussed how the
campaign finance system works and close with Perot's ideas on how
citizens should demand that Congress reform the laws governing
political campaigns and fund raising. 
