<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Attend Hamburg Trade, Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania and Germany are
jointly working on preparations for the Hamburg Trade and
Investment Conference scheduled for germany in September, this
year.
</P>
<P>
Director General of Tanzania's Board of External Trade (BET)
Mbarouk Mwandoro said here today that the event was aimed at
promoting trade and investment in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Frederick Sumaye will lead the Tanzanian
delegation to Hamburg, comprising officials from the ministries
of finance, and industries and trade, according to Mwandoro.
</P>
<P>
The Tanzanian team will also include local investors,
manufacturers and exporters.
</P>
<P>
Coordinated by the International Business Relations Committee
and the Germany Africa Association, the conference will be a
day-long event but will be followed by a four-day exhibition of
goods between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Director General stressed, "the conference will be an
important opportunity for Tanzanian businessmen to meet their
german counterparts and promote their businesses." 
</P>
