<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 204 Companies Privatized in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- A total of 204 companies and units
had been privatized in Zambia by the end of last month since the
privatization process started in 1992, Zambia Privatization
Agency (ZPA) said here today.
</P>
<P>
In a report, the agency also said another 33 companies are
ready under negotiations, 44 under preparation while 24 are on
probable liquidation or asset sale.
</P>
<P>
In addition, nine companies are under litigation, injunctions
and receivership and one under pre-privatization on preparation,
said the report.
</P>
<P>
It said that majority of the privatized companies have
retained most of their workers while a few sent all their workers
on forced redundancies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
