<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Has Heavy Debt Burden: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Zambia is one of 33 African
countries with huge external debt burden, Finance Minister Ronald
Penza said here today.
</P>
<P>
He said the debt burden continues to hinder development and
poverty eradication.
</P>
<P>
Despite African efforts, the stock of debt has continued to
increase, said the Zambian minister.
</P>
<P>
He said that the poverty eradication programs that have been
put in place by various African governments will not bear fruits
if the debt burden is not reduced.
</P>
<P>
Penza urged the donor community to assist African countries in
their efforts to attract foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that poverty eradication in Zambia is a must
if the country is to achieve sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
Zambia's foreign debts stand at seven billion U.S. Dollars
with each and every Zambian shouldering 800 Dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
