<HEADLINE> 0408033 Nigeria to Be Self-Sufficient in Cement by 2003 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria will be self-sufficient in
cement by the year 2003, Chairman of the Cement Manufacturers
Association of Nigeria Chief J.O. Makoju has said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a seminar in Port Harcourt on Monday, Makoju, who
is also Chief Executive of the West African Portland Cement
Company, said Nigeria is abundant with raw materials for cement
production in all parts of of the country and could be
self-sufficient if the existing facilities operate well.
</P>
<P>
He called on the government to fund the expansion of the eight
existing cement plants so as to enhance their capacity
utilization.
</P>
<P>
The chairman lamented that since 1991, Nigeria's cement
production has been on the decline while increasing import have
gulped millions of Dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
