<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bosnian Company Reports Big Revenue Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Energoinvest reported today that
the Bosnian conglomerate had registered a 133 percent increase in
revenues in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The revenues were worth 230 million German marks (138 million
US dollars) in 1996, of which 46 million marks (27.6 million
dollars) was earned from exports.
</P>
<P>
According to the company's steering board, its workforce
accounts for 1.37 percent of the total in the Bosnian Federation
and the average salary paid by the company is 59 percent higher
than that of the federation.
</P>
<P>
In January, the total employment of the federation was 338,181,
while the average salary was 238 marks (142.8 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Energoinvest was one of the industrial giants in the former
Yugoslavia, employing more than 20,000 workers in its heyday.
</P>
<P>
The current production is only one-tenth of pre-war levels, the
steering board reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
