<HEADLINE> Bosnian Presidency Agrees on Central Bank Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The Bosnian presidency on Tuesday
agreed on the basic solutions for the functioning rules of a
central bank, the local press reported.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the presidency said that its members have
asked the bank's steering board to prepare bills based on the
agreed solutions, which will be discussed during the next session
of the presidency. It is still unclear what they have agreed upon.
</P>
<P>
Bosnia's central bank has already had a steering board
consisting of one member each from the three ethnic nation, but
the Muslims, Serbs and Croats have yet to agree on a law governing
the central bank.
</P>
<P>
The passage of the central bank law and legislation currency,
customs and foreign trade in Bosnia are pre-conditions set out by
the international community for holding a donors' conference to
offer further economic assistance to the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
