<HEADLINE> UK Government Backs Tight Controls on Meat Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The British government has
indicated that it would support proposals on tightening controls
of meat processing industry in the wake of the fatal E-coli
outbreak.
</P>
<P>
The BBC television quoted Scottish Secretary Michael Forsyth as
saying today that the British government would endorse proposals
on separation of raw and cooked meats and use of separate staff
wherever possible.
</P>
<P>
A report into a recent E-coli outbreak in central Scotland,
which killed 18 people, also stressed that animals should arrive
for slaughter in a "clean condition".
</P>
<P>
It also urged hygiene standards at all British abattoirs to be
"rigorously enforced" in an effort to avoid similar incidents in
the future.
</P>
<P>
The Scottish Federation of Meat Traders said that the
recommendations would make the industry safer and boost consumer
confidence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
