<HEADLINE> Shanghai-Rhone-Alpes Memorandum of Understanding Signed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 9 (Xinhua) -- A memorandum of understanding on
friendly exchanges between Shanghai and the Rhone-Alpes Region of
France was signed in Shanghai today.
</P>
<P>
According to the memorandum, the two sides will cooperate in
trade and the economy, science and technology, education,
agriculture, environment, personnel training, and culture through
next year.
</P>
<P>
The chairman of the region, Charles Millon, attended today's
signing ceremony with Shanghai's Mayor Xu Kuangdi .
</P>
<P>
Xu presented Millon with the "White Yulan Magnolia" award,
given by the Shanghai municipal government to foreign friends and
experts for their contributions to Shanghai's economic
construction and social development.
</P>
<P>
Since the forging of friendly relations between Shanghai and
the Rhone-Alpes Region in 1986, both sides have had fruitful
cooperation in trade and the economy, science and technology,
agriculture, and environment, in which Millon has played an
important role. 
