<HEADLINE> Finns Enjoy Longest Paid Holidays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BONN, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Finnish workers on average enjoyed
46.5 days of paid holidays in 1996, the longest among the
industrialized countries.
</P>
<P>
The Cologne-based Institute of Germany Economy (IW) said
Wednesday that next to the Finns were Italians and Germans, with
43 and 40.8 days on average, respectively.
</P>
<P>
United States workers were at the end of the list with only 23
days, compared with 31 days enjoyed by Japanese workers, the IW
said. 
</P>
