<HEADLINE> IBM To Increase Investment in South China Economic Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 9 (Xinhua) -- A senior official with the US's
IBM said that the blue giant intends to put 50 million US dollars
more into one of its joint ventures in Shenzhen, a special
economic zone in south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
William Bowle told Xinhua at an opening ceremony Tuesday for
the Shenzhen Hailiang Storage Products Co. Ltd. that it is IBM's
largest venture in China.
</P>
<P>
