dollars into the venture, with IBM holding an 80-percent stake.
</P>
<P>
The venture will produce magnetoresistance head, a key
component of the computer's hard drive. The company is expected
to set up 20 production lines this year and have a capacity of 36
million heads annually.
</P>
<P>
IBM already has two joint ventures in Shenzhen, producing
electronic boardcards and other computer components. 
