<HEADLINE> Commercial Bank Branch Supports Shanghai Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai branch of the
nation's biggest state-owned commercial bank, the Industrial and
Commercial Bank of China, has helped the local economy by focusing
on industrial giants.
</P>
<P>
More than three quarters of the bank's loans last year, or 11.2
billion yuan, were with large enterprises or enterprise groups in
Shanghai, according to the president of the bank, Shen Ruolei.
</P>
<P>
It also was the sponsor of 26 industrial giants in Shanghai,
providing them with more than six billion yuan in funding for
expansion last year, and keeping a close watch on their management
for greater efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The bank also funneled another 2.87 billion yuan into the
Pudong New Area, which will become an economic force behind
Shanghai's economy.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the bank's assets were above 220
billion yuan, and its 1996 profits rose to a record high of 2.56
billion yuan. 
</P>
