<HEADLINE> Chang Moved into Second Round at Hong Kong Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Michael Chang completed
an easy 6-0, 6-1 win over unranked wild card entry Melvin Tong of
Hong Kong in the first round of the Salem Open here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chang held a 3-0 first set lead on Tuesday before the match was
halted because of rain.
</P>
<P>
Chang's serve, speed and powerful groundstrokes turned out too
march for the inexperienced Tong and the tournament favorite
completed the game by lossing only on set.
</P>
<P>
Tong was with the Hong Kong Davis Cup team who beat Saudi
Arabia 4-1 in Riyadh over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
Chang now faces American Jeff Tarango in the second round.
</P>
<P>
In other games Wednesday, South African Neville Godwin upset
the Czech Republic's Martin Damm 6-4, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Australia's fifth seed Patrick Rafter came from a set down to
score a 2-6, 7-6 (7-5), 6-4 win over compatriot Mark Woodforde.
</P>
</TEXT>
