<HEADLINE> Nuclear Experts Arrive in DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, April 9 (Xinhua) -- A 54-member nuclear experts team
from a multi-national consortium arrived today in the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) to negotiate the building of
nuclear reactors in the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
The team of the Korean Peninsula Energy Development
Organization (KEDO), is a consortium led the United States, South
Korea and Japan, which was formed under a 1994 nuclear deal. It
arrived in the eastern coastal city of Sinpo by ship from the
South Korean eastern port of Tonghae. 
</P>
</TEXT>
