<HEADLINE> Agricultural Cooperation Between Israel and Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Israel and southwest China's
Yunnan Province have agreed to increase agricultural cooperation,
according to a local source.
</P>
<P>
An economic and trade delegation of representatives of 15
Israeli enterprises, led by Israeli Ambassadress to China Ora
Namir, arrived in the provincial capital of Kunming this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Namir noted that there is huge potential for Sino-Israeli
economic cooperation, particularly in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with Namir, Yunnan's governor He Zhiqiang said
that his province has vast land and favorable climate for
agricultural development, but that farming technology in the
province is outmoded. The province urgently needs Israeli
agricultural technology, he said.
</P>
<P>
Both sides expressed a desire to expand cooperation in other
economic fields as well. 
</P>
</TEXT>
