<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 130.39 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market today gained 130.39 points to
3,650.88 as against 3,520.49 on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The national index jumped by 53.16 points to 1,578.37 from
1,525.21 previously.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and US dollar index were quoted up at 352.74 and
341.28 compared with Monday's 341.28 and 158.41 respectively.
</P>
<P>
After a moderate setback on Monday, speculative surged up to a
strong finish on the BSE market today in the wake of heavy
speculative buying.
</P>
<P>
Though foreign institutional investors and local institutions
evinced no interest due to the fluid political situation in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Operators covered their short-sale positions in view of
positive developments at the Center starting negotiations between
the Congress and the United Front to hammer out a formula to
resolve the political crisis out of the Congress withdrawal of
support to the United Front on March 30.
</P>
<P>
Operators seemed confident about the survival of the government
as no party wants the mid-term poll in the country at this stage.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
