<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets With Japanese Economic Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
said here today that China is trying to improve its investment
environment and make a special effort to provide a favorable
environment for overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
He made this remark when meeting today with a Japanese business
delegation headed by Tetsuro Kawakami, chairman of the Kansai
Economic Federation.
</P>
<P>
Li said he is happy to see Japanese businessmen investing in
China's Yangtze River Valley and in the central and western
regions.
</P>
<P>
China is intensifying its efforts to develop the central and
western regions, which are rich in resources, have a huge market,
and have great potential for cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Kawakami said the Kansai business people are willing to foster
trade and economic ties with China, and participate in the
development of the central and western regions. They would like to
strengthen trade and economic cooperation, technology transfers,
and personnel training, he said.
</P>
<P>
Wu Yi, Chinese Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, was also present at the meeting.  
