<HEADLINE> Chinese Red Cross Provides Relief for Quake-stricken Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The China Red Cross Society today
announced it is allocating 200,000 yuan to provide temporary
shelter for victims of two earthquakes in Xinjiang on April 6.
</P>
<P>
The earthquakes, measuring 6.3 and 6.4 on the Richter Scale,
hit Jiashi County in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Initial losses were estimated at 670 million yuan. According to
local sources, the tremors affected 290,000 people in 13 townships
and 296 villages; 38,700 houses were destroyed; 1,824 head of
livestock were killed.
</P>
<P>
An hour after the first quake, the local red cross society and
healthcare institutions sent three medical teams to the area. The
CSRC has also received 750,000-US-dollars worth of medicines and
equipment donated by a US foundation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
