<HEADLINE> Northeast China Garment Maker Has High Hopes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The China Dayang Enterprise Group,
one of the largest garment-makers in the country, challenged
popular brand-name products today when it came out with its own
"Dayang Brand".
</P>
<P>
Li Guilian, general manager of the company, held a news
conference here today to promote its garments and fashions, where
he said, "Dayang Group is aiming at world markets by designing and
exporting its own brand of fashions."
</P>
<P>
Li told a gathering of 500 people, which included Vice-Chairman
of NPC Standing Committee Cheng Siyuan, State Councilor Peng
Peiyun and Vice-Chairman of CPPCC National Committee Sun Fulin,
that each year, the group produces nearly 10 million suits,
raincoats, and sportswear outfits, and exports 81 million US
dollars worth of goods to 25 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The company has opened dozens of chain-stores in northeast and
north China, and recently a fashion shop run by Dayang and two
foreign firms was set up in Chicago. Dayang also plans to enter
European and Asian markets, she said.
</P>
<P>
There are now more than 30 foreign experts or fashion designers
working for the group, she said, which is also involved in
electronics, chemicals, and real estate.
</P>
<P>
She revealed that the company is expected to be listed on the
domestic stock exchange this year.
</P>
<P>
Bo Xilai, Dalian's mayor, told Xinhua that Dayang is the
largest township-based enterprise in his city, and that the city
government has always helped firms like Dayang that are trying
hard to produce quality goods.
</P>
<P>
In reference to the booming garment industry in the coastal
city, Bo said that, although the clothing industry merely accounts
for a small proportion in the city's industrial production, the
industry has gained nationwide fame thanks to local factories.
</P>
</TEXT>
