<HEADLINE> Romania Fired National Team Trainer Over Doping Cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Romanian national team trainer
Eugen Raducanescu has been fired for repeated doping cases
involving his athletes, according to the Romanian Athletics
Federation (FRA) said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Raducanescu was sacked from the technical staff of Romania's
national team for repeated proven doping charges against his
athletes," FRA president Iolanda Balas said.
</P>
<P>
The FRA banned four athletes who were trained by Raducanescu
for periods of two to four years. Three of them were women
athletes who tested positive for nandrolone, one of the most
powerful anabolic steroids in use.
</P>
<P>
Junior 400-meter world champion Andreea Burlacu, also in
Raducanescu's charge, was banned for two years. 
</P>
