dominated market action after the release of the Wallis Report
today, but other blue chip industrials also spurred the Australian
share market to a strong finish.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed 20.3 points higher at 2389.2
points after reaching an intraday high of 2,392.7.
</P>
<P>
The banking index initially fell sharply after the release of
the Wallis Report, but a surge in National Australia Bank and
Commonwealth Bank shares resulted in the index closing 27.4 points
higher at 4,113.6.
</P>
