<HEADLINE> Guangdong to Issue Visa Hong Kong Dollar Card </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 9 (Xinhua) -- China's first Visa credit card
based on Hong Kong dollars will soon be issued in some cities of
the southern Guangdong Province, the card issuer Guangdong
Development Bank announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong, neighboring Hong Kong, which returns to China on
July 1, is the country's economic powerhouse which has received
billions of investment dollars from Hong Kong businessmen.
</P>
<P>
"This is a terrific gift for Hong Kong's return, and it will
help enhance the economic and cultural ties between the inland
provinces and Hong Kong," a bank official said.
</P>
<P>
The Visa card, to be sold mainly to consumers in Guangdong,
Macao and Hong Kong, will enable card bearers to purchase at 13
million stores around the world, and to draw their money at the
290,000 Visa/Plus automatic teller machines (ATM).
</P>
<P>
The American AT&AMP;T China branch also promised that Chinese card
bearers holding GSM telephones (Global Service of Mobile
Communication) can pay their service bills with the card.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong Development Bank is the first Chinese issuer of the
Visa card valid both at home and abroad. It set up a Visa/Plus ATM
at the Baiyun Airport in April.  
</P>
</TEXT>
