<HEADLINE> Century-old Prison in Malaysia to Be Turned into </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 9 (Xinhua) -- A century-old prison in
Malaysia's capital city will be turned into a museum.
</P>
<P>
The Pudu prison building in the downtown, built in 1891,
comprising six blocks with 130 cells each, closed on November 1,
1996 after some 1,700 convicts were transferred to another prison
outside the capital city.
</P>
<P>
The prison-turned museum, the first of such kind in the
country, will be formally opened on May 3, Prisons Department
Director Zaman Khan told a news conference at the prison
headquarters in Kajang Prison some 20 kilometers away from here.
</P>
<P>
He said that the museum would initially open for six months but
may be extended, based on public response.  
</P>
</TEXT>
