<HEADLINE> One More Person Dead in Hong Kong Flats Blaze </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 9 (Xinhua) -- A 44-year-old woman, who was
staying in hospital in critical condition after Tuesday's fire in
a residential block, was certified dead this afternoon, bringing
the death toll to eight.
</P>
<P>
Another woman in intensive care was declared brain dead, the
Hong Kong Government Information Service (GIS) said.
</P>
<P>
There are still five fire victims staying in hospitals, who are
in stable or satisfactory condition.
</P>
<P>
The fatal blaze broke out at Mei Foo housing estate in Kowloon
at noon Tuesday and was put out two hours and a half later.
</P>
<P>
The toll released by the GIS Tuesday evening was seven dead,
including two baby girls, and 38 others injured.
</P>
<P>
It was the third major blaze within five months. Last November
the Garley Building fire killed 39 people and injured 81, while in
January 1997, an arson in a Tsim Sha Tsui karaoke bar killed 17
people.  
