<HEADLINE> Trading on HK Stock Exchange Rises in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Market trading on the Hong Kong
Stock Exchange rose in March after a contraction in February.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest monthly report from the exchange,
average daily turnover for the 19 trading days in March was 10.239
billion HK dollars (1.32 billion US dollars), an increase of 18
percent over the previous month.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover value for the month was 194.532 billion HK
dollars (25.1 billion US dollars), up 24 percent from that in
February.
</P>
<P>
A total of 94.135 billion shares changed hands in March,
compared with 73 billion in February. The average daily turnover
by volume was 4.95 billion shares, up 22 percent from February.
</P>
<P>
Average daily turnover for the first quarter of this year was
10.213 billion HK dollars (1.32 billion US dollars), up 67 percent
from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover by value during the quarter was 597.25 billion
HK dollars (77 billion US dollars), up 59 percent from the same
period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
A total of 283.234 billion shares were traded during the first
three months of this year, compared with 139.48 billion shares
during the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index at the end of march was 12,534.32, a fall
of six percent compared with the previous month but an increase of
14 percent over a year earlier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
