<DOCNO> XIE19970409.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Index Steady On Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Share prices increased early
today but declined later on the Singapore market with the
benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index closing virtually
unchanged as it fell by only 1.51 points to reach 2,103.2 points.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 153.35 million units, worth
352.69 million Singapore dollars (about 244.92 million US
dollars). Declines led advances by 180 to 127, while 298 other
counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Ber Ind. continued to be the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 12.34 million units. It was followed by
Westmont Land which had 6.18 million shares traded. MBf Holdings
was next with 4.82 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Airlines (SIA) Foreign led the gainers of the day
as it rose by 20 cents to finish at 12 Singapore dollars. Venture
Mfg gained 16 cents to end at 3.92 dollars, while Elec picked up
by 14 cents to close at 4.9 US dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 and the Overseas Chinese Banking
Corporation (OCBC) Foreign were the biggest losers of the day as
each of them declined by 50 cents to close at 17.8 and 18.1
Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Local property developer City Development fell by 40 cents to
finish at 13.7 Singapore dollars, while the Development Bank of
Singapore (DBS) Foreign and the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH)
Foreign lost 30 cents each to end at 18.7 and 27.2 Singapore
dollars respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
