<HEADLINE> Number of Industrial Casualties Drops in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The number of industrial casualties
dropped 12.5 percent in 1996 from the previous year in Macao,
latest statistics from the Macao Census and Statistics Department
show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the department show that 14 people died in
industrial accidents last year. Thirteen of them were male, and
their ages ranged between 25 and 44.
</P>
<P>
The release said that construction industry was the most
dangerous sector.
</P>
<P>
In addition, 3,747 people were injured last year, up 10.5
percent from 1995. The injured were of 25 years to 44 years old.
</P>
<P>
Of the injured, 831 were migrant workers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
