<HEADLINE> Thai Man Charged with Drug Smuggling in Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 9 (Xinhua) -- A Thai man has been charged with
smuggling heroin into Saudi Arabia, a local newspaper reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The man, identified as Abdul Torlaeb, was arrested at Jeddah
airport on March 18 when Saudi officials said that they found 290
grams of heroin worth 1,200 U.S. dollars hidden in a special belt
and in his rectum, the Bangkok Post said.
</P>
<P>
This was the first case on heroin smuggling into Saudi Arabia
involving a Thai, the newspaper quoted Thai diplomats in Jeddah as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The 36-year-old man from Thailand's southern province of
Pattani arrived in Saudi Arabia on March 17 with his wife, ready
to make a pilgrimage to Mecca. He said he carried the heroin for
personnel use.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said that Abdul could face the death penalty.
</P>
</TEXT>
