<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets Vietnamese Army Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Chairman of China's Central
Military Commission (CMC), State Councilor and Defense Minister
Chi Haotian met here today with a delegation from military area
commands in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese delegation is led by Dao Trong Lich, commander
of the Second Military Area in Vietnam. The group arrived in
Beijing on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in the Great Hall of the People, Chi said
that the two countries are brotherly neighbors with a long history
of friendship. He said that leaders of the two armies have
exchanged visits at all levels since the normalization of
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
He said that visit by Dao and his entourage is of great
significance for the further development of the friendship and
relations of cooperation between the two countries and their
armies.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the two countries should be far-sighted and
consider the overall situation of bilateral relations to promote
friendship and cooperation on the basis of the five principles of
peaceful co-existence.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries share a common belief and common
goals, and both are faced with the challenge of securing peace and
development.
</P>
<P>
The strengthening of relations between the two armies will
enhance the friendship between the two countries and the two
peoples, he said.
</P>
<P>
Dao said that China's reform and opening up, economic growth
and modernization of the army are very impressive. He said he
wishes that the two armies will step up exchanges and cooperation
at all levels, so as to improve cooperation between the two
countries in all fields.  
</P>
</TEXT>
