<HEADLINE> Syrian FM to Visit Russia Shortly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 9 -- Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq al-Shara
will pay an official visit to Russia next week in a fresh
diplomatic effort to save the stalled Middle East peace process,
diplomatic sources disclosed here today.
</P>
<P>
The upcoming visit to Moscow by the Syrian foreign minister is
a completion of a European tour intended to explain Syria's
position on the Middle East peace process and reactivate the
Russian role in this process.
</P>
<P>
Russia and the United States are two co-sponsors of the Middle
East peace march.
</P>
<P>
Arab states welcome the Russian and European roles in
achieving a just and comprehensive peace in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the U.S. and Israel have reservations about
the Russian and European roles in the Middle East peace
process. 
</P>
