<HEADLINE> Seven Children Killed by Vietnam Wartime Bomb </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Seven school children were killed
and 32 others injured when a bomb left over from the Vietnam War
exploded, the Vietnam News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The fragmentation bomb, buried under ground, went off Monday at
a boarding school in Vietnam's central province of Nghe An, as
school children were leaving their school.
</P>
<P>
The bomb was left over from a U.S. air strike against northern
Vietnam during the Vietnam War, which ended more than 20 years
ago.
</P>
<P>
The explosion was due to the tremors of hundreds of school
children leaving classrooms.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the incident, local authorities and medical
workers rushed to the scene to treat the injured children. 
</P>
</TEXT>
