<HEADLINE> China Lists Key Educational, Agricultural Construction Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- China has added to a list of key
national construction projects for 1997 a plan to construct or
renovate a total of 100 universities over the next century, and a
project to produce five billion kg of open market grain.
</P>
<P>
Named on the list are 129 projects, covering a wide range of
industries, which have been named as major state construction work
for this year by the State Planning Commission (SPC). Each of the
plans will enjoy preferential treatment, especially in terms of
funding.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the two new projects, the list also contains
schemes involving light industry and textiles; one in
pharmaceuticals; two electro-mechanical and auto projects; the
third-phase construction of the forest protection belt in
northeast, north and northwest China; and one vaccination program
initiated by the Ministry of Public Health.
</P>
<P>
Five other projects, including one for grain circulation and
supported by World Bank loans, are also included on the list.
</P>
<P>
SPC yesterday urged relevant central and local government
departments and financial institutions to give full support to the
work. 
</P>
