south of Tokyo, said the Meteorological Agency.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of injuries or damage.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at 12:50 local time (0350 GMT), was
centered at 50 kilometers beneath the seabed near the island, the
agency said.
</P>
<P>
Japan, one of the world's most quake-prone countries, has
experienced moderate to strong tremors in recent weeks on its
southern areas. 
