<HEADLINE> China Increases Efforts on Railway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- China will undertake 15 key
national railway construction projects this year, to ease the
bottleneck of transportation caused by economic development, the
State Planning Commission said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Among them are the Southern Xinjiang Railway project, the
Nanning-Kunming Railway, and the Baoji-Chengdu Railway electric
project.
</P>
<P>
China will add 6,000 km to its 58,000 km-railway network during
the Ninth Five Year Plan period (1996-2000); the 15 designated
projects are part of this work.
</P>
<P>
The nearly 1,000-km Southern Xinjiang Railway, started last
year, will link the resource-rich region to east China upon its
completion by the end of this century.
</P>
<P>
The Nanning-Kunming Railway, which became operational last
month, is aimed at promoting the economic development in China's
backward areas.
</P>
<P>
The electric project will contribute to the nationwide efforts
to raise the speed of train cars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
