<HEADLINE> China Publishes List of Key Water Control Projects for 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- China has listed eight projects as
key water control construction tasks in 1997, the State Planning
Commission has disclosed.
</P>
<P>
On the list are the central program for comprehensive treatment
on Taihu Lake; the Xiaolangdi Water Control Project along the
middle reaches of Yellow River; the Jiangya water control project
in central China's Hunan Province; a project to harness the Huaihe
River; and the Wanjiazhai water control project in north China's
Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The list also includes three projects initiated and undertaken
by local governments: the Uruwat water control project in
Xinjiang; a comprehensive agricultural irrigation and resettlement
development project on the Shule River of Gansu Province and
another scheme, also in Gansu, to divert water from Datong River
into Qinwangchuan.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports, China has named 129 projects as
key national construction projects for 1997, of which 68 are
related to energy.
</P>
<P>
Projects listed out as key national construction projects will
enjoy a number of priorities, especially bank loans. 
