<HEADLINE>   New Cypriot Ministers Sworn in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Five new Cypriot ministers,
appointed after Tuesday's first reshuffle of President Glafcos
Clerides' cabinet, were sworn in this morning.
</P>
<P>
During an official ceremony at the Presidential Palace, in
the presence of President Clerides, first minister to give the
prescribed affirmation was new Foreign Minister Yiannakis
Cassoulides, an ex-government spokesman who replaced Alecos
Michaelides.
</P>
<P>
The other four ministers are Justice and Public Order
Minister Nicos Koshis, who replaced Alecos Evangelou; Education
and Culture Minister George Hadjinicolaou in the post of Claire
Angelidou; Communications and Works Minister Leontios
Ierodiaconou, who replaced Adamos Adamides and Health Minister
Christos Solomis in the post of Manolis Christofides, who was
appointed as the new government spokesman.
</P>
<P>
President Clerides pointed out to his new ministers that they
have taken over "very responsible posts" and he wished them every
success.
</P>
<P>
Six other ministers in the eleven-member cabinet have kept
their posts.
</P>
<P>
They are Minister of Finance Christodoulos christodoulou,
Defense Minister Costas Eliades, Interior Minister Dinos
Michaelides, Commerce, Industry and Tourism Minister Kyriacos
Christofi, Labor and Social Insurance Minister Andreas
Moushoutas and Agriculture Natural Resources and Environment
Minister Costas Petrides.
</P>
<P>
President Clerides took office in February 1993, and the next
presidential elections will take place in February 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
