Velayati noted "Our embassy in Beirut has already released a
statement on that case. We have a lot information that they were
kidnaped by the extreme rightists and transferred over to
Israel."
</P>
<P>
An anonymous spokesman for the Iranian Embassy in Beirut said
earlier that there are proofs and evidences that four Iranian
nationals are still alive, who were kidnaped in east Beirut in
1982.
</P>
<P>
On the front pages, the Iranian press published the names and
pictures of the detainees, identified as Taqi Rastegar Moghaddam,
Ahmad Motevasselian, Mohsen Mousavi and Kazem Akhavan.
</P>
<P>
The embassy spokesman said that his embassy would pursue the
matter through appropriate channels as before. 
</P>
</TEXT>
