<DOCNO> XIE19970409.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Suspends Loans Backed up by Deposit Receipts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- China's central bank has issued a
notice ordering the suspension of loans backed by deposit receipts
and the strengthening of management over term deposits.
</P>
<P>
Loans backed deposit receipts as a mortgage, excluding those to
individuals backed by personal savings of less than 100,000 yuan
(about 12,000 US dollars), will no longer be granted as of April
21, the People's Bank of China said in the notice.
</P>
<P>
The mortgage-backed loans yet to mature will be examined one by
one, the notice said. And the financial institutions will not
issue receipts to the units that deposit money and will instead
issue a certificate to verify that the units have opened a deposit
account, it said.
</P>
<P>
The certificate cannot be used for a mortgage, the notice
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The central bank reiterated that the receipts designed for
savings deposits must not be used for deposits of the units and
the misused receipts must be withdrawn before May 30. It said that
savings posts are not allowed to accept deposits by units.
</P>
<P>
The commercial banks must not exceed the ceiling imposed by the
central bank of the special receipts used for savings deposits,
the notice said.
</P>
<P>
The PBC will formulate the management rules on the extension of
loans backed by deposit receipts as a mortgage, and the business
can only be resumed afterward, the notice said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
