<HEADLINE> Iranian President' Visit to Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Iran said today the timetable
for the visit by President Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani to Saudi
Arabia has not been finalized.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Minister Ali Akbar Velayati said at a press
conference here that Rafsanjani was invited to make an official
visit to the Gulf kingdom during his recent meeting with Saudi
Crown Prince Abdullah Ibn Abdul Aziz on the sideline of the
Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC) meeting in Islamabad,
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
"But when the trip would be materialized is yet to be decided
upon," said the Iranian foreign minister.
</P>
<P>
However, a well-informed source said that Rafsanjani is
expected to make the trip after the Haj ceremonies instead of
April when the holy performance is conducted.
</P>
<P>
The source disclosed that Rafsanjani is now fully occupied.
</P>
<P>
But, some observers here said that Rafsanjani might not
receive an official invitation from King Fahd of Saudi Arabia
because of pressures from the United States.
</P>
<P>
However, Velayati said that Iran's relations with the Gulf
countries are growing. The recent meetings between him and
officials of the Gulf countries show that Iran and the countries
of the region are determined to mend ties, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We are at the beginning of the new chapter for the relations
with them. We have already implemented the first part of the
initiative that they have asked by our trips to Saudi Arabia and
the Persian Gulf states," Velayati said.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian government has launched an active drive to seek
support from heads of state of the Islamic countries for the
OIC summit meeting due in Tehran in December.
</P>
<P>
Velayati made his multi-nation tour in March carrying messages
from Rafsanjani to his counterparts, requesting them to attend the
December OIC meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
