<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-09 10:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Gulf Sea Cable to Start Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 9 (Xinhua) -- A new cable under the Gulf
sea waters linking Kuwait, Bahrain, Qatar and the United Arab
Emirates (UAE) will start operation in July this year, official
sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The 1350-kilometer-long cable called "Fog" would provide high
technological services in transmitting video, audio and facsimile
signals, in addition to providing data for all computers and
Internet users in the four countries, said the sources from
Kuwaiti Communication Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The cable was also designed to link with other international
cables like "Flag" which would stretch through the Red Sea and
Arabian sea to Europe after it comes into operation by the end of
this year.
</P>
<P>
Linking Fog and Flag will connect the Gulf with Japan, China,
Thailand, Malaysia, India, Egypt, Italy, Spain, Britain and other
countries.
</P>
<P>
They said the cable was designed to live for up to 25 years,
but studies show that it might serve for 50 years without regular
maintenance.
</P>
<P>
The cable runs from Kuwait through Bahrain and Qatar all
the way to the UAE. Saudi Arabia has also requested to join
the cable, the sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
