<HEADLINE> South China Enforces Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 9 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong Province
has closed 512 of the 529 enterprises designated by the State
Council as sources of serious pollution problems, according to the
latest statistics.
</P>
<P>
The province has redoubled its efforts at combating pollution
over the past year. It has defined many protection areas for
drinking water sources. The construction of waste water treatment
factories has been speeded up.
</P>
<P>
With the growth of solid waste dumping, the province
established a center to manage it last year. As a result, over 600
tons of waste materials imported illegally was uncovered.
</P>
<P>
The province's capital city has decided that automobiles must
control pollution from their exhausts. The provincial government
is also increasing its efforts at controlling noise.  
</P>
</TEXT>
