<HEADLINE> China Lists Out Key Coal Construction Projects in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- China will focus its attention on
19 key projects for coal construction this year, information from
the State Planning Commission disclosed.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, most of these projects are located in
the coal-rich areas in northern, eastern, northeastern and central
parts of China.
</P>
<P>
Four major coal projects will be built in Shanxi Province,
dubbed a "sea of coal," two in Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region,
two in Heilongjiang Province, two in Anhui Province, two in
Shandong Province, three in Henan Province, one in Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region, one in Shaanxi Province, one in Hebei Province
and the one in Gansu Province.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports, China has named 129 projects as
key national construction projects for 1997, of which energy
projects account for 68. 
