<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Publishes List of Six Major Oil Projects in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- China has listed six projects as
major petroleum development tasks this year, information from the
State Planning Commission disclosed.
</P>
<P>
The projects are situated in the northeastern, northwestern and
eastern areas of China.
</P>
<P>
They are: development at Daqing Oilfield of Heilongjiang
Province; exploration at Liaohe Oilfield of Liaoning Province;
development at Shengli Oilfield of Shandong Province; development
at Xinjiang Oilfield (Karamay) and oil exploration at Tarim Basin
of Xinjiang; and development at Changqing Oilfield of
Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia region.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports, China has named 129 projects as
key national construction projects of 1997, of which 68 are
related to energy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
