<HEADLINE> Cuban FM Arrives for Visit to Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Cuban Foreign Minister
Roberto Robaina arrived here today for a five-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
Roberto Robaina is the first high-ranking official of the Cuban
government to visit Malaysia with which Cuba has no diplomatic
ties presently.
</P>
<P>
His visit here is seen as a move toward the establishment of
diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
His visit reciprocated that made by Information Minister
Mohamed Rahmat to Cuba last February in his capacity as National
Front secretary- general.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban foreign minister is expected to call on Malaysian
Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad and Deputy Prime Minister Anwar
Ibrahim tomorrow and is also scheduled to hold talks with his
Malaysian counterpart Abdullah Ahmad Badawi on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Robaina will also meet Malaysian businessmen and deliver a talk
entitled "Cuba: The Challenges To Defend The Sovereignty, The
Development and The Independence" at the Institute of Diplomacy
and Foreign Relations here.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban minister, who is on a tour of Asian countries, will
leave for Brunei on Sunday after his visit here.  
</P>
</TEXT>
