<HEADLINE> ROK Insurance Giant to Open Office in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Samsung Fire and Marine Insurance
Co. Ltd., is expected to open its Shanghai Office on April 17, according
to Jin-Won You, the company's chief representative in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first insurance firm of the Republic of Korea
(ROK) to open an office of this kind in the Chinese metropolis.
</P>
<P>
Chief Representative You said his company is confident that
China's insurance market has great potentials and that Shanghai is
the most important insurance center in the country.
</P>
<P>
For geographical and historic reasons, ROK businessmen used to
do business mainly in Liaoning Province in the northeast and
Shandong Province in the east, but now more ROK firms have come to
Shanghai and its adjacent provinces and cities owing to the booming
economy in Shanghai, You said.
</P>
<P>
Almost all major ROK firms have opened offices, ROK-solely
owned companies, or set up joint ventures in the vicinity of
Shanghai, and financial companies of ROK have also showed great
interest in the area, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the representative office will try to get
acquainted with the local market and laws regarding the insurance
business, and it will prepare for the setting-up of the company's
Shanghai Branch in future.
</P>
<P>
According to You, the ROK insurance giant, founded in 1952, is
one of the oldest in his country, and in April of 1995, the
company opened its Beijing Office, its first office in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
