<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan to Develop New Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The island province of Hainan
Province has witnessed sustained economic growth by developing
new industries such as automobiles, chemicals, metallurgy and
textiles.
</P>
<P>
The new industries serves as a driving force behind local
economic development, and helped the island province achieve a 13
percent of growth in industrial output value last year.
</P>
<P>
Hainan, also China's largest special economic zone, produced
431,000 motor vehicles, 45,000 tons of polyester chips, and 30,000
tons of cold-rolled steel sheets last year, up 58 percent, 600
percent and 400 percent over 1995, respectively.
</P>
<P>
It produced 16,000 tons of urea since October last year, which
is a new chemical product for the province.
</P>
<P>
It intends to expand and complete construction of 14 industrial
projects in the coming two years, involving the production of
polyester chips, fertilizers, tin-plated sheets, and beer.
</P>
<P>
The new industrial projects are expected to help the province
get more than one billion yuan in industrial added value this
year.
</P>
<P>
This year the province will give priority to construction of
projects in the fields of fertilizers, paper pulps, automobiles,
fiber-optics, and nylon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
