<HEADLINE> PKK Kidnaps 4 Village Guards in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Rebels of the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK) have kidnapped four village guards in
Diyarbakir, center of the southeastern Turkey, Anatolia News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that a group of the PKK militants searched
some houses in Lice town of Diyarbakir Tuesday night and
kidnaped four village guards.
</P>
<P>
The rebels also molested the Tepe village of Town Lice a few
days ago and seized nine people including the head of the village
and one village guard.
</P>
<P>
Turkish security forces conducted large-scaled operations in
the region in a bid to rescue the kidnapped, said the Anatolia
report.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a separatist war for self-rule since
1984, which has claimed over 21,000 lives in the east and
southeast of Turkey including PKK members, government troops and
citizens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
