<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing helps Rural Residents Shake off Poverty. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 9 (Xinhua)-- Chongqing, which became a
municipality directly under the central government last month, has
listed poverty relief at the top of the government's
agenda.
</P>
<P>
Three other key problems confronted by the municipal government
are resettlement of one million people living in the Three Gorges
dam areas on the middle reaches of the Yangtze River,
upgrading of existing enterprises, and environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
Of the 43 counties and districts under the jurisdiction of New
Chongqing, 21 are poverty-stricken areas with a total population
of 3.66 million, 15 percent of the city's rural population.
</P>
<P>
The annual per-capita income of farmers in these poor areas are
less than 500 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Delin, secretary of the Chongqing Municipal Committee of
the Communist Party of China, pledged that the local authorities
are determined to lift these people out of poverty within three
years.
</P>
<P>
To attain the goal, the municipal government will build more
communications and telecommunications facilities in poor areas to
enable them to enhance economic and trade ties with developed
areas.
</P>
<P>
Large groups of technicians will be sent to rural areas to pass
modern agro-techniques onto farmers.
</P>
<P>
More infrastructure, industrial projects, and service centers
will be built in poor areas.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government will provide each poor county with
100,000 yuan to develop rural public health and another 100,000
yuan to develop education, annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
