<HEADLINE> Academy Gets Aid from Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The government of south China's
Guangdong Province has provided 50 million yuan to the local
branch of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS) since they signed
an agreement in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two years, the Guangzhou branch of CAS has gotten
financial support from the provincial government in terms of
construction of key labs, an engineering research center, the
infrastructure, and the improvement of the living standards of the
science workers, according to a spokesman for the CAS branch.
</P>
<P>
The CAS branch has embarked on a number of projects concerning
agriculture, disaster relief, environmental protection, sustained
development, the development of oceanic resources, and basic
construction in line with the province's plan for economic and
social development in the coming five years.
</P>
<P>
While strengthening the academy's research facilities, the
provincial government has spent more than 10 million yuan
renovating the academy's office building.
</P>
<P>
Starting last July, the provincial government set aside more
than 1.8 million yuan annually to subsidize the medical care of
the academy's staff. 
</P>
</TEXT>
