<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tiger Skin Sellers Arrested in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Prosecutors of Huanren Man
Autonomous County in northeast China's Liaoning Province recently
approved the arrest of seven people for selling tiger pelts, an
endangered species, according to local informed sources.
</P>
<P>
Local policemen in January caught three sellers and confiscated
a tiger skin at the trading spot. Four suspects related to the
case were seized a fortnight later.
</P>
<P>
The people confessed the skin was transported into China at a
border trade fair. They purchased the skin at 50,000 yuan and
hoped to sell it at 100,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Local animal protection officials identified the skin as that
of the Northeast Tiger, an endangered species prohibited to trade
worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The case is still in the process of court hearing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
