Ibrahim tomorrow and is also scheduled to hold talks with his
Malaysian counterpart Abdullah Ahmad Badawi on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Robaina will also meet Malaysian businessmen and deliver a talk
entitled "Cuba: The Challenges To Defend The Sovereignty, The
Development and The Independence" at the Institute of Diplomacy
and Foreign Relations here.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban minister, who is on a tour of Asian countries, will
leave for Brunei on Sunday after his visit here.  
