<HEADLINE> Uganda Sets Up Disaster Committees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan government has
established disaster preparedness and management committees at both
national and district levels, announced Vice President W. Kazibwe
here yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Six million US Dollars have been released as funds to fight
hunger and poverty in the country, Kazibwe was quoted by today's
daily ''the Monitor'' as saying.
</P>
<P>
In 18 of all the 45 districts in the country, Kazibwe said,
about 341,000 people are facing the prospects of full scale food
insecurity, whereas 1.5 million have experienced food
shortages due to various reasons.
</P>
<P>
Kazibwe said, ''the government will continue to facilitate training
of stockists, intermediary agencies and beneficiaries in the
management of water for agriculture, inputs, credit and disease
control.''
</P>
<P>
North and northeastern Uganda is often attacked by
severe drought in dry seasons from December to next March, causing
starvation and even death to some victims. enditem

