<HEADLINE> SADC Members Meet to Coordinate Maritime Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Member countries of the Southern
African Development Community (SADC) on Tuesday opened their
first meeting on sea and river transportation as part of the
regional integration bid.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of the meeting said SADC members are striving for
unifying their maritime policies, protecting coast environment,
enhancing port operation efficiency and cut transport costs.
</P>
<P>
"We are trying to speak in a sole voice in the maritime
legislature," said Carlos Bambo, coordinator of the meeting,
noting that laws concerning maritime affairs are different in
different countries.
</P>
<P>
Delegates hoped a "navigation control fleet" could be
established to supervise maritime activities in the whole
southern African coastal region. 
