<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poor County Becomes China's Top Walnut Kernel Producer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Zanhuang County, Hebei
Province in North China, once a poverty-stricken area, has become
the largest walnut kernel production center in the country.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the county processed and exported 3,500 tons of such
kernel valued at nearly 100 million yuan, which accounted for over 30
percent of the country's total walnut kernel market share.
</P>
<P>
The county, which is rich in walnuts and sweet dates as well as
some minerals such as limestone and silicon stone, started to
process and export walnut kernels which are exported to a dozen
countries and regions including ROK, Japan and Canada.
</P>
<P>
Currently, 60 firms and over 700 local people have been
engaged in marketing walnut kernel, while the number of locals
involved in processing the product has exceeded 6,000.
</P>
<P>
China is the third largest walnut kernel producer in the world
after India and the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
