KIEV -- Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma Tuesday appointed
Seigei Tiginko as the new first deputy prime minister in charge of
the country's economic reforms, replacing Viktor Pinzenik, whose
resignation was accepted by Kuchma on Monday.
</P>
<P>
ROME -- The Italian Senate Tuesday approved a government
resolution to send Italian soldiers to join the multinational
protection force to crisis-ridden Albania. 
