<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese Legislator Meets Japanese Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Senior Chinese legislator Wang
Guangying said here Tuesday that China and Japan have a great
potential in developing economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Wang, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese
National People's Congress, made the remarks when meeting with
Shinji Sato, international trade and industry minister.
</P>
<P>
Sato said that China's rapid economic development can greatly
promote the Japanese economy as the economies of the two countries
are complementary.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese government supports Japanese businessmen to invest
in China's Three Gorges hydropower project, said Sato.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who arrived here Sunday for the first Sino-Japanese
entrepreneurs meeting, also met with Soichiro Ito, speaker of the
Japanese lower house Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ito said the entrepreneurs meeting will definitely boost the
bilateral economic cooperation and friendship. 
