<HEADLINE> Beijing Mayor Welcomes Japanese Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Beijing expects to expand
economic, trade, personnel, and financial ties with the Sumitomo
Corporation of Japan, Beijing Mayor Jia Qinglin told Miyahara
Kenji, president of the corporation.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with the Japanese visitor and his entourage
Tuesday, Jia Qinglin said that the corporation has broad business
ties with China, and that Beijing will bring in more foreign
funds in opening wider to the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
The mayor said that Beijing has decided to give top priority to
the development of high-tech industries, the service sector,
modern agriculture, electronic and automobile industries, and
apartment construction industry.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that cooperation with foreign companies
will be expanded in these areas.
</P>
<P>
Kenji Miyahara expressed the intention of furthering
Sino-Japanese friendship and contributing to China's economic
expansion.
</P>
<P>
Sumitomo has funded a dozen projects in Beijing. In 1996, trade
volume between the two sides reached 1.2 billion US dollars, with
Beijing exporting 500 million US dollars worth of goods to Japan.
</P>
<P>
Total trade volume between China and Sumitomo was 5.3 billion
US dollars last year. The latter has invested 900 million US
dollars in China. 
