<HEADLINE> Dongshan Island Aims to Become Largest Abalone Production Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 9 (Xinhua) -- A total of 25 abalone farms have
gone into operation on Dongshan Island in east China's Fujian
Province, involving an investment of 60 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities are ambitious to turn the island into the
largest abalone production base in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to local authorities' plan, the island will turn out
10,000 tons of abalone annually in 2000, with an estimated output
value of 2.2 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The island, located at the southern tip of the province, faces
the Taiwan Straits and is a suitable habitat for abalone. Since a
businessman from Taiwan introduced abalone to the island in 1992,
the island has become the largest abalone production base in
Fujian.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the island produced more than 200 tons of abalone
and cultivated 50 million items of abalone, which brought to the
island 200 million yuan in output value. 
</P>
</TEXT>
