<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Festival Featuring Ancient Battle Planned </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and overseas tourists
interested in the history of China's Three Kingdoms period
(220-280) are invited to attend a cultural festival featuring one
of the most well-known battles of that period starting May 28 in
Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
Visitors can have access to numerous historical records and
relics and visit sites where the Chibi Battle was fought in the
year 208, during the festival to be held in Puqi City, Hubei
Province.
</P>
<P>
The battle, resulting in the defeat of the larger troops led by
Cao Cao, by the smaller troops of Sun Quan and Liu Bei, was
decisive in creating the three kingdoms of the Wei, Shu and Wu.
The battle is frequently cited as a textbook example of military
tactics.
</P>
<P>
The city, where the battle was fought, built an exhibition
center, a tablet corridor, and a street to display the numerous
relics left from the battle.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day festival, there will be an international
seminar on the battle; a trade fair; and exhibitions on the
achievements of the Puqi City and its products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
