<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peony Brings Cash to Central China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUOYANG, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Peony, traditionally regarded as
the most beautiful flower in China, has made the economy bloom
for the ancient Chinese capital city of Luoyang, Henan Province in
Central China.
</P>
<P>
With the assistance of local scientists, who have determined
the schedule of the blossoming, the flower has been turned from a
mere showpiece to a commercial item.
</P>
<P>
Many new species of peony have been created and planted
citywide. The city has 30 peony cultivating bases, covering a
total of 173.3 ha. and planted with 4,8 million peony-trees in
over 800 species.
</P>
<P>
The city government has provided local peony growers with
preferential policies in taxation, funding, and export.
</P>
<P>
Annually, the city exports over 260,000 peony-flowers and
-shoots, earning over 52 million yuan from the exports. Luoyang
peony has been sold to foreign countries like the United States,
Japan, Germany, Holland, and Australia.
</P>
<P>
Even a Sino-US peony-planting joint venture with an investment
of two million US dollars was set up last year, which exports all
its productsand earned 400,000 US dollars in the first
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
