<HEADLINE> Minnesota of U.S. Declared Disaster Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 8 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
today declared the flood and snow-ravaged state of Minnesota a
federal disaster area.
</P>
<P>
The move will make available federal emergency funds, such as
grants, low-interest loans and emergency housing, to local
governments and individual victims in 21 counties.
</P>
<P>
Press reports reaching here said the flooding has already
displaced up to 5,000 Minnesotans.
</P>
<P>
The adversity was compounded over the weekend, when freezing
rain and snow downed countless utility lines in northwestern
Minnesota, leaving an estimated 50,000 people without power Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Some power had been restored, but repairs would take up to
seven days to complete, the state's emergency management director
said. 
</P>
