<HEADLINE> Nepal to Begin Local Elections Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Elections for over 4,000 local
administration bodies throughout Nepal will begin next month,
According to the country's Election Commission.
</P>
<P>
The commission announced Tuesday that the local elections will
be held in two phases in the country's five development regions.
</P>
<P>
The elections for villages and municipalities in the Western,
Mid-Western and Far-Western regions will be held on May 17 while
those in the Central and Eastern regions are slated for May 26,
Chief Election Commissioner Bishnu Shah told a press conference
here.
</P>
<P>
Elections for all the 75 district administrations, or the
District Development Committees, are scheduled for June 20, Shah
said.
</P>
<P>
The announcement of exact dates for the forthcoming local
elections came just days after the government issued an ordinance
to amend the country's existing laws concerning the local bodies
and their elections.
</P>
<P>
The Election Commission will follow the ordinance as a law
governing the local elections regardless of whether it is passed
or not by parliament, the chief election officer said.
</P>
<P>
A senior opposition leader earlier warned that the ordinance
could lead to a constitutional crisis in the country if
implemented without parliamentary approval.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali parliament concluded its winter session early this
month, just three days before the government issued the ordinance
concerning the local elections.  
</P>
</TEXT>
