<HEADLINE> Russia, Lebanon Seek Close Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
today said the resumption of talks between Syria and Israel,
Lebanon and Israel is of great significance to reactivating the
stalled peace process in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin today met visiting Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Al
Hariri in Kremlin and they discussed the situation in the Middle
East, said Sergei Yastrzhembsky, Russian presidential press
secretary.
</P>
<P>
Sergei expressed Russia's concerns over the armed conflicts in
southern Lebanon, especially over Israel's unilateral decision to
build Jewish settlements in the Arab quarters of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
He said Russia will steadfastly support Lebanon's independence
and sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
The implementation of United Nations resolution 425, Israeli
withdrawal of troops from occupied arab land and a pledge of
security for both Lebanon and Israel are critical to the
settlement of the southern Lebanon issue, added Sergei.
</P>
<P>
Hariri, who arrived here Monday for a three-day visit, has
signed two agreements with his Russian counterpart Viktor
Chernomyrdin on cooperation in science, culture, education, trade
and economy.
</P>
<P>
Hariri is the first Lebanese prime minister to visit Russia in
50 years since Lebanon established diplomatic relations with
Moscow. 
</P>
