<HEADLINE> East China's Island City Uses Computer Networks to Protect Egrets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The coastal city of Xiamen in
Fujian Province is increasing its residents' awareness of natural
conservation and bird protection through a computer network.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen is an island city and the original home of egrets for
many years in Fujian Province. The city, once called "egret
island," was famous for its tens of thousands of egrets living
there.
</P>
<P>
The computer network covers the Regulations on the Management
of Dayu Island Egrets Natural Reserve, the species of egrets,
their modes of life and habits. Residents can also learn how to
protect egrets.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, a number of egrets have returned to the
island. The city established the Dayu Island Egrets Natural
Reserve. 
</P>
