<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Tightens Supervision over Insurance Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The central bank has vowed to
further rein in the country's insurance industry this year to
prevent financial risks and promote the sound development of the
insurance industry.
</P>
<P>
During its first ever national conference on insurance
supervision held in Xiamen, Fujian Province, the People's Bank of
China pledged to quicken the pace of insurance legislation and
rectify the insurance market by shutting down illicit
insurance agencies and brokerage firms and standardizing insurance
activities.
</P>
<P>
"All the illegal insurance activities will be seriously
penalized and a national checkup of the assets of the insurance
companies will urge them to reduce bad assets," said an official
with the supervisory department of the People's Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
Insurance industry associations will also be set up soon
throughout the country for better self-discipline in the industry
and halt devastating competition, he said.
</P>
<P>
China's insurance market has expanded noticeably in recent
years, with its premium income jumping 26 percent to 77.6 billion
yuan last year, and the insured value reaching 15.67 trillion
yuan, up 15 percent over the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
