<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen: Bids for Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen in South China's
Guangdong Province has been experimenting with selecting designs
for its construction projects through public bidding since March
10 this year.
</P>
<P>
Local officials explained that they made the decisions based on
thorough research conducted by construction experts of successful
examples and opinions of designers from overseas.
</P>
<P>
According to the officials, the city has also promulgated a set
of provisional measures regarding management over bidding on ideal
designs of construction projects. The measures, which became
effective in early March, are aimed at standardizing management
over bidding on designs and safeguarding fair competition, as well
as protecting the legitimate rights of bidders and bid initiators.
</P>
<P>
Since the implementation of this new system, the city's land
administration has requested that a design submitted for approval
should not only include a detailed engineering configuration of
the project itself, but also contain proposals for environmental
protection and structuring of the neighborhood as a whole. 
</P>
</TEXT>
