<HEADLINE> Seeds Safely through at Bausch and Lomb Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 8 (Xinhua) -- All of the seeded players won
their opening matches at the Bausch and Lomb tennis championships
in Amelia Island, Florida on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
But the tournament lost third-seed Monica Seles who was forced
to withdraw because of bronchitis.
</P>
<P>
Second-seeded Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario of Spain came from first
set down to beat Florencia Labat of Argentina 3-6, 6-2, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Sapin's fourth-seeded Conchita Martinez edged South
Africa's Joannette Kruger 6-3, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Fifth-seed Anke Huber of Germany defeated Radka Zrubakova of
Slovakia 6-2, 6-2 and American Mary Joe Fernandez, the ninth seed,
easily downed Sarah Pitkowski of France 6-3, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
Other results saw 11th seeded Mary Pierce of France took an
easy victory over Germany's Elena Wagner 6-0, 6-1 while 13th seed
Brenda Schultz-McCarthy of the Netherlands outclassed Adriana
Gersi of the Czech Republic 6-1, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Seles, a finalist at Hilton Head last weekend and due to play
fellow-American Jennifer Capriati, had to withdraw just hours
before she was due on court. Argentina's Oliva Diaz took Seles'
place in the draw. 
</P>
</TEXT>
