<HEADLINE> Remote City Hooked up with National Telecom Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Lanzhou, capital of northwest
China's Gansu Province, has shortened its distance with the outside
world thanks to the opening of a public information network.
</P>
<P>
The Lanzhou Public Information Service Network, hooked up with
Chinanet, the country's national telenet linked with Internet, now
provides access for local users to surf on the information highway.
</P>
<P>
Based on recognized networking technologies, the subscribers
now can dial in the net and sort out information as they require.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said that the current database is divided into 17
information categories with contents covering such beats as news,
finance, securities, material supply, tourism, transport and
telecommunications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
