<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A music recital to honor the contributions of the late
leader Deng Xiaoping was held in Beijing yesterday evening. Senior
Party official Hu Jintao told the performers that their simple art
form expressed the common feelings of the Chinese people for Deng.
</P>
<P>
-- Liu Huaqing, vice-chairman of the Central Military
Commission, met with Charles Millon, the first French Defense
Minister to visit China since the two countries set up diplomatic
relations in 1964.
</P>
<P>
-- The paper's overseas edition reported that China's industrial
development was normal during the first quarter of this year with
an 11 percent year-on-year increase in the production with
value-added output reaching 452.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen Guofang said at a press
conference Monday that China hopes that those countries that still
insist on making an ant-China motion at the UN human rights
conference will decide to stop confrontation.
</P>
<P>
-- Zhang Tong, president of the China Great Wall Industry
Corporation, died in an accident during his visit to France's
Guyana Space Center.
</P>
<P>
-- Vice-Premier Qian Qichen on Monday expressed the hope that
Taiwan authorities will no longer prevent entrepreneurs from
investing in the mainland.
</P>
<P>
"China Youth Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- "Project Hope", the national fund-raising program to help
students in poverty-stricken areas, has collected 978 million yuan
(117.8 million US dollars) over the past eight years, allowing 1.5
million youngsters to return to schools.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Arthur Dunkel, former director-general of the General
Agreement on Tariffs and Trade, said in Shanghai that he was
optimistic about China's accession to the World Trade Organization
(WTO).
</P>
<P>
In the final accession plan, he said, a package deal must be
available that includes such key issues as China's foreign trade
rights and State-owned business.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Portuguest Joint Declaration on the Question of Macao,
which was signed 10 years ago, has produced positive results under
friendly co-operation between China and Portugal, Wang Qiren,
director of the Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch, said yesterday.
 
</P>
