<HEADLINE> Chinese Military Delegation Ends Visit to Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, April 8 (Xinhua) -- A military delegation led by
Zhang Wannian, vice chairman of China's Central Military
Commission, ended its four-day visit to Chile today.
</P>
<P>
Upon leaving for Brazil, the Chinese delegation was seen off at
the Santiago International Airport by Ricardo Izurieta, Chief of
Staff of Chile's National Defense.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, Zhang told Izurieta that he was very happy
to see his visit playing an active role in enhancing mutual
understanding and furthering friendly ties and cooperation between
the two countries, two peoples and two armies.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his gratitude for the hospitality shown by
Chile's state and military leaders.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Zhang held talks with Chilean President
Eduardo Frei, acting National Defense Minister and Interior
Minister Carlos Figueroa, Army Commander in Chief Augusto
Pinochet, Navy Commander in Chief Jorge Martinez, Air Force
Commander in Chief Fernando Rojas and Director General of the
uniformed police Fernando Cordero on matters of common interest.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation, which left Argentina for Chile last
Friday on the second leg of its three-nation South America tour,
also visited some Chilean military factories and installations.
</P>
</TEXT>
