<HEADLINE> Moya Struggles in Estoril Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Carlos Moya struggled
in his first round match against Spanish qualifier Jacobo Diaz at
the the Estoril Open tennis tournament in Oeiras on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Moya, ranked eighth in the world, won the first set 6-4 but
after rain stopped play for one hour he appeared to lose his
rhythm.
</P>
<P>
Diaz snatched a 6-1 victory in the second set and was three
games up in the third before Moya fought back to take the final
set 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, Carlos Costa took the first set off fellow
Spaniard Alberto Berasategui but soon lost momentum and the fifth
seed rallied to win 3-6, 6-2, 6-2.
</P>
