<HEADLINE> Five Cops Killed in Southern Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Five policemen were killed today
by unidentified gunmen near Sukkur, 350 kilometers northeast of
Pakistan's southern port city of Karachi, sources said.
</P>
<P>
The policemen were ambushed this afternoon by the gunmen when
they were going to their post in the riverain area of Kashmore,
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said four of them were killed on the spot and the
fifth succumbed to injury in hospital whereas all of the gunmen,
which is believed to belong to a local gang, had managed to flee.
</P>
<P>
The police in the area are waging an anti-dacoit movement in
order to improve the law and order situation there, they said.
</P>
</TEXT>
