<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Modern Pig Venture under Construction in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Work on a Sino-Singporean joint
venture featuring pig raising and trading has started at Chongming
Island in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, which covers an area of 1,300 ha, will be a
complex which includes pig raising, butcher, meat-packing, and
marketing.
</P>
<P>
It will be completed at a total cost of 100 million US dollars
in seven years. It will turn out one million pigs annually upon
operation, believed to be the largest pig complex in the world.
</P>
<P>
The first phase includes construction of 42 pig-pens equipped
with feeding, sterilizing, monitoring, and breeding facilities
imported from Japan and the United States.
</P>
<P>
The first group of 450 pigs imported from Denmark have mated
with each other and the sows are expecting to give births next
month.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that pig's dung will be used to grow flowers,
trees, and for aquatic cultivation after microbiological
treatment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
