<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Le Petit Prince" to Be Staged in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- "Le Petit Prince", a French fairy
tale for adults, written by Antoine Saint-Exupery, will be
performed on stage here from April 17 to May 3.
</P>
<P>
"Le Petit Prince" describes the human world through the eyes of
a little prince coming from another planet. It was revised into
a play and has been popular for several decades worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Chinese director Dai Rong has set the play in a traditional
bar. Saint-Exupery, a World War II pilot, tells of his experience
in the Sahara after his plane was shot down, when he and the
little alien prince made contact.
</P>
<P>
Dai said that she tried to make the drama full of humor and joy
and reveal people's heart-felt passion hidden behind the complex
society.
</P>
<P>
Actors and actresses of the drama, with an average age of less
than 25, are graduates or students of Central Drama Institute and
the Beijing Film Academy. They received support from the French
Embassy in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
