<HEADLINE> AS Roma Signs Swedish Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 8 (Xinhua) -- AS Roma fired Argentine coach Carlos
Bianchi on Tuesday and signed 74-year-old Swede Nils Liedholm to
replace him through the end of the season.
</P>
<P>
Bianchi, who joined the Italian first-division team last year,
became the sixth Serie A coach sacked during this season.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine was fired only two days after the club suffered
its eighth league loss, 2-1 to Cagliari on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Liedholm, who retired as a coach a few years ago, returns to
the team that he led to the Italian title in 1983. 
