<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's Eligible, Obligatory for China's National Games: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa
</P>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) will compete in international sports
events under the name of "Hong Kong, China" and it is eligible and
obligatory for SAR to participate in China's National Games,
HKSAR's Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa said here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
And the HKSAR government will give its full support to any
decision and efforts leading to forming a HKSAR delegation for the
Eighth National Games slated for October this year, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
The Chief Executive made these comments during his first ever
meeting here today with local sports celebrities including leading
members of the Sports Community for the Celebrations for the
Handover of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He praised local sports community for their contribution to a
smooth handover and to Hong Kong's continued prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong will usher in a new era 84 days from now and so will
Hong Kong's sports, Tung said. As HKSAR will be represented at
international arena as "Hong Kong, China," Hong Kong athletes are
encouraged to win honor for the people of SAR and for their
motherland, Tung continued.
</P>
<P>
As to the National Games, Tung said that as HKSAR is part of
China, it is only eligible and obligatory for SAR to compete in
the Games, and he ensured a full support from the SAR government.
</P>
<P>
He called on all members of the Hong Kong sports community and
the whole society not to miss this chance as all the Chinese
provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions are making
efforts to form their sports delegations for the Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
