stumbled again amid fear about inflation and interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rallied over the final half
hour, adding 53.25 points to 6,609.16. In the past three sessions,
the gauge of 30 big U.S. companies has recovered about 130 of the
400 points it lost over the previous five sessions.
