<HEADLINE> Al Chief: Economic Cooperation Possible Only After </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of the Arab
League (AL) Esmat Abdul Meguid said today that regional
economic cooperation can not be materialized unless a just and
comprehensive peace is realized in the region.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here today from the Bahraini
capital of Manama, Meguid made the remarks in his speech at the
fifth Gulf Economic Symposium, which opened today under the theme
of "international strategies and relations by the turn of the 21st
century among the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) states."
</P>
<P>
Meguid said that recent incidents that took place in the region
will exert important influence over some regional countries,
thus complicating the ongoing peace talks between Israel and Arab
countries concerned.
</P>
<P>
The Al chief stressed that Arab countries adhere to peace,
which is their strategic choice. The Arab countries have
consistently made efforts to realize this choice so as to achieve
security and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
For this purpose, Meguid said, the Arab world has long agreed
to realize a just, durable and comprehensive peace in the Middle
East. 
</P>
</TEXT>
