<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kofi Annan Urges Zaire to Cease Hostilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 8 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General Kofi
Annan today urged both rebel force and government to firm up their
stated commitment to a total cessation of hostilities.
</P>
<P>
In a statement on the first direct talks on the future of Zaire
held in South Africa, Annan welcomed the news that the Alliance of
Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Congo-Zaire and the
government established a positive working relationship and
outlined a transition process to a peaceful and democratic Zaire.
</P>
<P>
"I am encouraged that the parties reaffirmed their support for
the UN/OAU peace plan and committed themselves to transparent,
fair and inclusive elections to bring about democratic change in
Zaire," he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the political family of Zaire will
work together to build a peaceful future.  
</P>
</TEXT>
