<HEADLINE> Zairean President Declares State of Emergency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Zairean President Mobutu Sese Seko
today declared a state of emergency on all the territory of the
country, as the rebels are at the door of the copper-producing
center Lubumbashi, reported Agence France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
Zairean television said that the state of emergency was
declared at the proposal of the government.
</P>
<P>
According to the Zairean Constitution, the president can "take
the urgent measures to stand up to the situation."
</P>
<P>
Direct negotiation between government representative and rebel
representative scheduled for this week in South Africa has been
postponed, and the rebels of Laurent-Desire Kabila have vowed to
go up till Kinshasa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
